<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Disruptive_innovation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="reflist columns references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-Christensen2003p_xviii-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Christensen2003p_xviii_1-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Christensen2003p_xviii_1-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Christensen2003p_xviii_1-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFChristensen1997">Christensen 1997</a>, p.&#160;xviii. Christensen describes as "revolutionary" innovations as "discontinuous" "sustaining innovations".</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-FOOTNOTEChristensen200349-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEChristensen200349_2-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFChristensen2003">Christensen 2003</a>, p.&#160;49.</span></li>
